= Introduction =

Whonix for Windows is designed to be a simple introduction for newcomers. It enables people to experiment with Whonix in a familiar environment without the necessity of complex imports or host operating system changes.

As you learn more about how to use Whonix, do not forget that Windows cannot provide a secure foundation for Whonix operations.

= Download, Verify and Install Whonix =

'''Step 1: Download the Installer'''

[https://download.whonix.org/windows/Whonix-Installer.exe Whonix-Installer for Windows]

'''Step 2: Verify the Installer'''

Download the [https://download.whonix.org/windows/ego.asc signing key] and the [https://download.whonix.org/windows/Whonix-Installer.exe.asc installer's signature].

[[Installer/Verify_the_Installer_using_the_command_line|Verify the installer]] on the command line.

'''Step 3: Install Whonix'''

Execute the verified Whonix-Installer.exe and follow its instructions. <ref>https://www.whonix.org/wiki/DoNot#Do_not_Change_Settings_if_the_Consequences_are_Unknown</ref>

